First — Understand What You're Actually Building
HackerRank/LeetCode test: "Write a function that reverses a linked list."
→ Candidate writes code → it runs → tests pass or fail → done.
Your platform test: "Build an agentic workflow that takes a user question, searches the web, summarizes results using an LLM, and handles errors gracefully."
→ Candidate thinks with AI → prompts a model → reviews generated code → accepts/modifies → executes → observes agent behavior → iterates → done.
These are completely different evaluation paradigms. You're not testing "can you code" — you're testing "can you think and build with AI agents" — which is the most valuable skill in 2026 and nobody has a platform that evaluates it properly yet.

